ads.author: Glenn Musto
ads.title: Atari Tempest Arcade Machine – 1981 Classic Reproduction, w/ modern electronics
ads.description:
Modern Re-Creation of the Legendary 1981 Atari Tempest

Step back into the golden age of arcades\u2014without the headaches of vintage hardware.
This is a brand-new machine built in the style of the iconic Atari Tempest, faithfully recreating the sights, sounds, and gameplay of the original classic.

Authentic Gameplay

As a Tempest champion in the 1980s and owner of an original machine, I can personally vouch that 
the gameplay here is spot-on, indistinguishable from a brand-new Tempest as it played in arcades back in the day.

Why This Machine Is Better

The truth is, the original Tempest was a maintenance nightmare. Its color X-Y CRT monitor burned itself out, circuit boards constantly failed, and many machines ended up in the dump. That\u2019s why working originals are nearly impossible to find\u2014and even if you do, you\u2019re stuck battling those same issues.

This machine eliminates every one of those problems, while giving you more:

24" LCD with LED backlighting (IPS panel, any-angle viewing \u2014 no fragile CRT).

New spinner with dual sealed bearings for silky-smooth precision control.

50-watt stereo sound system with subwoofer, volume control pod, and headphone jack (not just old mono sound).

Commercial-grade power: 500+ watt ATX supply plus built-in 1,000-joule surge protector with EMI/RFI filtering.

Universal JAMMA harness for plug-and-play swap of other JAMMA boards.

Durable build: \u00be\u201d commercial-grade cabinet, stainless steel control panel hardware, polycarbonate overlay and graphics (not scratch-prone vinyl).

LED marquee lighting (no hot fluorescent bulbs).

Poly wheels that roll without scratching floors.

Freeplay setup for home use (no quarters required).

Choice of keyed vault-style lock or thumb lock for the front door.

Extra Features

Tempest & Tempest Tubes \u2014 play classic levels and unlock options never before accessible.

Levels 1 through 99 \u2014 explore stages you may have never reached in the arcade.

Demonstration Mode: blast through tubes, clear spikes, or jump levels instantly\u2014perfect for testing all 99 levels, whether you\u2019re a pro or a newcomer.

Why It Matters

This is not just another retro cabinet with emulation slapped inside.
It\u2019s a commercial-grade, modernized Tempest machine built to last a lifetime, with gameplay so accurate that arcade veterans can\u2019t tell the difference.

Full instructions come with order, including game options, settings, default settings, etc. Defaults are:

Game difficulty is Medium, 
Bonus Life awarded at 20,000 points, and 
3 lives per game.
Local pickup or buyer arranged packing and shipping. Game is located in Saint Petersburg Florida. If you want it shipped, I will make it available any time at my home for your freight company to pick it up. You must make all arrangements. 

Size at control panel - approx. 25" wide x 33" deep.

Heigth - approx. 73" cabinet top to floor with wheels.

Weight - approx. only 170 lbs. (thanks to the LCD/LED monitor).

Palleted shipping weight - approx. 210 lbs.

ads.author: Nick Mizgala
ads.title: Rebuilt Vintage 1990 Neo-Geo Metal Slug Arcade Cabinet $900
ads.description:
Up for sale is a 1990 SNK Neo Geo MV-1, 1 slot board in a Dynamo cabinet, with stereo sound and LED credit indicators. The cabinet was rebuilt and repainted in 2017, with new vinyl and t-molding installed. The marquee bracket, coin doors and coin bucket holder were also repainted. The only vinyl that is still original is the control panel, but plexiglass cover was replaced. The coin mechanisms are complete and functional, with matching locks for both coin doors, as well as the back cabinet door. It has a 19" Sharp Image CRT monitor with a beautiful and sharp (no pun intended) picture. It currently has 2" locking casters installed for ease of movement.

It currently has a Metal Slug cartridge installed, as the 161 in 1 multi-cart started to flake out. It is included with the sale. It plays well and has been stable, having been taken to Momo Con, Furry Weekend Atlanta and Southern-Fried Gaming Expo a few times over the years.

Given the age of this game, it is sold not DOA (Dead on Arrival), but otherwise as-is. It is local pickup only from Tucker, Georgia. Sale is starting at $900, with payment by cash or PayPal.

More pictures of the game and the rebuild are available here:
https://playeronearcadeservices.com/for-sale/neo-geo-rebuild/

\ud83c\udfae Atari Flashback 9 (AR3050 HDMI) Overview
Released on November 15, 2018, the Atari Flashback 9 (AR3050) is a plug-and-play dedicated retro console built by AtGames under license from Atari 

Comes pre-loaded with 110 classic Atari games, outputting at 720p via HDMI.

Includes two wired joystick controllers, along with an SD card slot for playing additional games, saving states, and receiving firmware updates 

\u2728 Features & Performance Highlights
HDMI output ensures crisp visuals on modern HDTVs without needing old-style composite cables 

The SD card slot allows custom ROM playback and easy firmware updates\u2014something users praise as a standout improvement over earlier models 

The built-in emulation uses the Stella emulator (v3.x) for Atari 2600 titles and handles gameplay smoothly.

ads.author: Tom Grizzard
ads.title: 1991 Konami Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles: Turtles In Time video arcade
ads.description:
Control one of the four Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles as you battle through different time periods (prehistoric to the future) in this horizontal scrolling fighting game. The cool "3-D" effect as you throw enemies at the screen and the funny speech ("Ooh, forgot the sunscreen!") make this game memorable.

Own a piece of video game history with this 1991 Konami Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles: Turtles In Time arcade game. Experience the thrill of battling Shredder and his minions with your favorite turtle heroes. This arcade machine is perfect for any collector or gaming enthusiast, featuring iconic graphics and classic gameplay. With Konami's reputation for creating some of the best arcade games of the era, this Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles game is sure to provide hours of entertainment. Whether you're reliving your childhood or introducing a new generation to the game, this arcade machine is a must-have. Don't miss out on the opportunity to own this piece of nostalgia.

Great condition. 

Everything works.

Will ship via freight carrier at Buyer's expense.  Local delivery available for nominal fee.

ads.author: Pei Huang Wu
ads.title: Gauntlet Legend Dark Legacy Arcade Game
ads.description:
Developer/Publisher: Midway Games (Arcade 2000, followed by home ports)  \ufffc \ufffc
Arcade System: Midway Vegas hardware, supporting 1\u20134 players in co-op mode  \ufffc

Gameplay: This expansion to Gauntlet Legends adds five new realms and four character classes (Dwarf, Knight, Jester, Sorceress), includes combo and turbo attacks, and features enhanced 3D graphics with character upgrades and voice guidance  \ufffc

Pricing - Then & Now

Original (Street) Price: When first released in 2000, the dedicated arcade cabinet retailed around $4,500\u20134,900, based on listings from restored cabinet resellers  \ufffc

VintageArcade.net lists Gauntlet Legends at $4,495 with a $200 upgrade option for Dark Legacy (totaling ~ $4,695), and some show ~$4,895 as well  \ufffc

Collector/Resale Prices Today:

Standard restored units typically sell between $4,000\u20135,500. For instance, Gameroom Goodies lists a fully refurbished Dark Legacy cabinet at $4,495\ufffc.

Premium or rare cabinets, including original parts or pristine condition, may command upwards of $8,000\u201311,000. A non\u2011Arcade-specialist site listed one at ~$11,200 retail (discounted to $8,500), though this may be an outlier due to bundled services  \ufffc.

Private sales/auctions tend to land around $1,000\u20131,500 in local deals, especially when open to conversion boards or disclaimers on condition (). More rare finds have been reported around $4,500

ads.title: Monster Bash Pinball
ads.description:
I shopped and LED'ed it and put it in our lineup. It's been rock solid & reliable.

It must have had cabinet wrinkle where the legs bolt to the cabinet because a previous owner covered the area in what looks like black vinyl. See pics. Otherwise, the game is in decent, solid, reliable condition.

It's more of a "players quality" game and is priced accordingly. It was routed at some point in its life and still has the coin door lock bar & mounts to prove it.

I'd never owned MB so I bought one that was on the lower end of the price range to see if I liked it. It's a fun game with easy to understand ruleset. Only putting it up for sale to help fund a grail car purchase in the near future.

Pinside suggested price is $9k. I think $8000 is fair for my MB.

ads.author: Stephen Savage
ads.title: Tekken 3 Arcade Cabinet – Solid Shape, Minor PCB Issues, Great Emulation Setup
ads.description:
Looking to sell my Tekken 3 showcase cabinet. It\u2019s in solid shape overall. The monitor and game were working the last time I powered it on, though it\u2019s been a while.
 \u2022 Game/Controls: Player 1 controls work fine. Player 2 controls have a couple of buttons that don\u2019t respond when playing Tekken 3 directly. However, when I connected a Raspberry Pi through a Pi2JAMMA device, all the controls worked. That suggests the issue may be with the Tekken 3 PCB, not the wiring or buttons.
 \u2022 Condition: Cabinet is big and heavy. It\u2019s been garage-kept and is in decent cosmetic condition.
 \u2022 Logistics: Please note, I cannot deliver and my ability to help move it is limited due to health reasons. You\u2019ll need a truck/van and at least two people to move it. 
 \u2022 Price/Offers: Open to reasonable offers. Mostly looking to find this machine a good home.

ads.author: Tom Grizzard
ads.title: 1992 Konami X-Men video arcade  (PLEASE READ COMMENTS)
ads.description:
1992 Konami X-Men video arcade game is a retro collectible arcade gaming machine that allows players to experience the popular X-Men franchise through interactive gameplay. With Konami's reputation for quality and innovation, this arcade game offers a nostalgic gaming experience for fans of the series and collectors of vintage arcade machines. Featuring the iconic X-Men characters and storyline, this video arcade game is a must-have for any gaming enthusiast looking to add a piece of arcade history to their collection.

THE GOOD: Cabinet is in great overall condition. Monitor has no issues. Joysticks work fine, might be loose for some likeness/favor but nothing a new centering grommet would not solve... and not seized for removal as I did remove to clean and made adjustments, and shafts were cleaned well so wouldn't seize in near future (for easy removal).

THE BAD:  Original gameboard took a dump on me, and cost to replace is hovering around $1000.00... so, I installed a Pandora's DX box (turning off all games except X-men, so boots directly into game) and wiring the player 3 and player 4 control in via two "USB Joystick" pcb wiring adapters. The Pandora DX does support 4 players in Konomi X-Men with only one quirk that is not an issue... when you start either player three or player four you get player three, followed by player four... no big deal at all... besides that one super minor quirk everything works as it should.  To be clear, you can play a three player or a four player game no problem, and you can pick who is each... you just get player 3 controls first regardless if you hit player 3 or player 4 start, followed by play 4 controls if you hit either player 3 or player 4 start after starting a 3 player game first.  I see no sound or video issues WHATSOEVER playing X-Men on the Pandora's Box DX... NONE!  

As a convenience, I added 4 free-play buttons just above each of the coin chutes (small red start push buttons like on 1980's midway cocktail tables, barely noticeable) on the two top coindoors for any home user purchase.... those can easily be taken disabled and the coin mechs for all four players work fine if buyer wishes to collected revenue.

Will ship via freight carrier at Buyer's expense.  Local pickup allowed and encouraged (zip 31525). Local delivery (from Savannah down to Jacksonville) available for nominal fee.

ads.description:
The Arcade1Up head-to-head Pac-Man table is a home arcade machine designed in the style of a classic "cocktail table" game from the 1980s. It is meant for two players sitting opposite each other, and it includes multiple games from the Pac-Man universe and other arcade classics. 
Head-to-head format: The machine is a tabletop, or "cocktail," arcade cabinet, with two sets of controls facing each other. This allows two players to sit and compete directly across from one another.
STOOLS INCLYDED IN UNOPENED BOX BRAND NEW
Hardware and display: The table is equipped with a 17-inch color LCD screen and a protective, clear top to guard against spills and dust. It features two control panels with full-size joysticks and buttons for an authentic arcade feel. Two speakers, one on each side, provide audio with adjustable volume.
Stools: While some retailers offer packages that include matching stools, they are typically sold separately. Arcade1Up sells its own line of branded, height-adjustable stools with chrome legs and padded seats that are compatible with the table.

ads.title: Could your small business use an extra source of income???
ads.description:
Hi! 

I own and operate arcade games like mini claw machines, cut 2 win games, etc. I am based out of enterprise

I place these machines in restaurants, play places, gyms, and more. Then of course pay the locations a commission on all plays. 

There is no cost to the locations, they just get paid a healthy commission. Great way to make money on unused space, as well as generate an entirely new draw to your establishment.

I would love to come some time and talk to you guys about getting one in y\u2019all\u2019s location. You would be amazed how many people continue to come back to some of my locations strictly to grab some food and play my claw machines.

My smallest claw machine only takes up 12 inches of floor space, and uses less than $5 per month of electricity!
